1 AN ACT relating to risk protection orders.
2 Be it enacted by the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of Kentucky:
3 SECTION 1. A NEW SECTION OF KRS CHAPTER 237 IS CREATED TO
4 READ AS FOLLOWS:
5 (1) As used in this section:
6 (a) "Firearm" has the same meaning as in KRS 237.060; and
7 (b) "Qualified mental health professional" has the same meaning as in KRS
8 202A.011.
9 (2) Proceedings under this section shall be initiated by the filing of a verified petition
10 in District Court.
11 (3) The petition and all subsequent court documents shall be entitled: "In the
12 interest of (name of respondent)."
13 (4) The petition shall be filed by a qualified mental health professional, peace officer,
14 county attorney, Commonwealth's attorney, spouse, relative, friend, or guardian
15 of the individual concerning whom the petition is filed, or any other interested
16 person.
17 (5) The petition shall set forth:
18 (a) Petitioner's relationship to the respondent;
19 (b) Respondent's name, residence, and current location, if known; and
20 (c) Petitioner's belief, including the factual basis for the belief, that the
21 respondent is or has been diagnosed with or treated for a mental condition
22 that causes or is likely to cause impairment in judgment, perception, or
23 impulse control to an extent that presents an unreasonable risk to public
24 health, safety, or welfare if the person were in possession or control of a
25 firearm.
26 (6) Upon receipt of the petition, the court shall:
27 (a) Set a date for a hearing within fourteen (14) days from the filing of the
